The Yemen government will observe a three-day  ceasefire following 15 days of fighting with southern forces, the  northern-controlled SABA news agency reported Friday.
The ceasefire, effective from Saturday 0:00 a.m. (Friday 2100 GMT), was  declared on the occasion of the Moslem Al-Adha festival prior to Sunday's  celebration of the fourth anniversary of the unification of South and North  Yemen, the agency said.
